comments.body:
I don't think it makes sense to ever include any of the `ALLOW_ANY` types in `forbid` (if you don't want a string, then in reality you probably `require` a boolean eg), so having:

```
  constexpr unsigned int ALLOW_ANY_EQUIV = ALLOW_BOOL | ALLOW_INT | ALLOW_STRING;
  
  assert((forbid & ALLOW_ANY_EQUIV) == 0);
  if (*flags & ALLOW_ANY) require &= ~ALLOW_ANY_EQUIV;

  ..

  return (*flags & ALLOW_ANY) == 0; // since ignore_types is gone now
```

might make sense?

